ases where your garage door is open or close by itself is the cause for your opener having a faulty logic board.";i:4;s:60:"The logic board or Circuit board is the brain of the opener.";i:5;s:89:"A faulty board will in most scenarios sometime cause the door to open or close by itself.";i:6;s:168:"The remedy is as KennethR did clear all devices from your garage door by holding the learn button for 30 seconds -and reprogram all of your openers to your garage door.";i:7;s:86:"And check that no neighbors are opening their doors when your programming you openers.";i:8;s:196:"The concept behind a garage door opener is that one press of a button will open and close the door helping reduce the stress strain and otherwise inconvenient task of manually performing this job.";i:9;s:138:"However there can be seemingly odd instances in which a door will open on its own without any interaction from the owner of the structure.";i:10;s:70:"Yes its possible although rare for your garage door to open by itself.";i:11;s:72:"There are a few unusual factors that can cause your door open by itself.";i:12;s:42:"Here are a few scenarios weve come across.";i:13;s:144:"Residential electric garage door openers manufactured after 1993 are equipped with two safety mechanisms that operate while the door is closing.";i:14;s:56:"The first is photoelectric and the second is mechanical.";i:15;s:63:"My Lift master garage door would just open up late at night an.";i:16;s:94:"This video will show you how I fixed my garage door from opening by itself seemingly randomly.";i:17;s:57:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Keeps Opening After Closing.";i:18;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:19;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:20;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:21;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:22;s:62:"If anything enters the beam even briefly the door opens again.";i:23;s:19:"Garage Door Opener.";i:24;s:27:"Opens and closes by itself.";i:25;s:162:"When your garage door opens or closes when you havent triggered the remote one possible cause is that a neighbors remote was programmed at the same time as yours.";i:26;s:53:"Erase all codes in your remote and then reprogram it.";i:27;s:183:"Incorrect travel settings When your garage door is installed the opener is programmed with a number that indicates how far down the door is expected to travel before its fully closed.";i:28;s:167:"If the door closes before that set distance has been completed then the opener thinks theres an error and automatically reverses to prevent property damages or injury.";i:29;s:95:"Below are three reasons why your garage door opens on its own and some quick fixes you can try.";i:30;s:53:"Garage doors use radio frequencies to open and close.";i:31;s:160:"Whether youre using the passcode entry the buttons inside the garage or your remote opener the openers and the garage door itself must be on the same frequency.";i:32;s:49:"Your garage door opens immediately after closing.";i:33;s:40:"The garage door keeps going up and down.";i:34;s:47:"Your garage door opens when it hits the ground.";i:35;s:39:"Garage door opener keeps going back up.";i:36;s:34:"It may be your garage door sensor.";i:37;s:101:"There are four common problems with garage door sensors three of these homeowners can fix themselves.";i:38;s:47:"Both of mine failed and were replaced for free.";i:39;s:90:"You will need to call customer service and provide the SN date code underneath the button.";i:40;s:81:"It needs to be remove from the wall to get to the info on the back of the button.";i:41;s:99:"One of my doors began to randomly open and close the other button started beeping and wouldnt stop.";i:42;s:77:"Your garage door is programmed to travel a certain distance before it closes.";i:43;s:138:"If it closes before that distance has been traveled it thinks something is wrong and it reopens to help prevent any damage or safety risk.";i:44;s:34:"But changes in weather conditions.";i:45;s:97:"It could be in the circuit board a remote the wall button or its wiring or even the wired keypad.";i:46;s:124:"Older Stanley garage door openers are known for opening and closing by themselves because of a malfunctioning circuit board.";i:47;s:89:"Defective remotes or ones with worn-out batteries will sometimes send out random signals.";i:48;s:101:"A garage door that randomly opens by itself is not a common problem but does occur from time to time.";i:49;s:161:"Garage door openers operate on one of many frequencies and while it is possible for one of your neighbors remotes to open your garage door it is highly unlikely.";i:50;s:86:"Newer openers operate on rolling codes making it almost impossible for this to happen.";}}